{
  "text": "This chamber was similar to the one described by [CITATION_1] . It contained a single inflow/outflow conduit and Ag/AgCI electrodes for monitoring light-evoked transretinal voltages (electroretinogram, ERG) . The incubation well volume was^-50 Al . Solutions were added and removed through the conduit by pipetting (Pipetman, with disposable tips ; Rainin Instruments, Brighton, MA) . ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29605903"
